      <t:profileDesc xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">
         <t:abstract><t:p>This is the general record to be used to refer to a collection described as ʾƎgziʾabǝḥer nagśa in cases where its type cannot be determined.
            There are three collections called ʾƎgziʾabǝḥer nagśa, two of which are <t:ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT4030EgziabeherN">ʾƎgziʾabǝḥer
                                                  nagśa (Giyorgis of Gāsǝḉḉā)</t:ref>
            and <t:ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT4031EgziabeherN">ʾƎgziʾabǝḥer
                                                  nagśa (Zarʾa Yāʿqob)</t:ref>. The third type probably began as <t:ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT1326egziab">ʾƎgziʾabǝḥer nagśa
                                                  za-ʿĀrke</t:ref>
            and through rearrangement and enlargement became <t:ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2001Mazmur">Mazmura fǝśśuḥān
                                                  wa-ṣalota tǝkkuzān</t:ref>.</t:p></t:abstract>
